CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 1, 1962 reads: "PIONEER'S FAMILY - Mal R. Goode, one of Pittsburgh's most prominent pioneers now is joining the ABC news department as a staff member.  Here he's shown with his lovely family.  Left to right, front row: Ronald, Mal, Mrs. Goode and Rosalia.  Standing: Roberta, Richard, Russell and Robert" (Daughter Roberta was inserted into published photo).
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Goode family, including sons Ronald, Richard, Mal Goode, son Russell Goode, daughter Roberta, Mary Lavelle Goode, and son Robert Goode, posed outdoors in front of their home in Belmar Gardens
